content: I don't think this works anymore. seems to just sit in waiting for sleep mode and never buzzes.

It works with new galaxy watch. It does what it's supposed to, it vibrates everytime I snore just enough to get me to roll over. The only problem is it vibrates everytime my wife snores also....lol....so I would never get sleep if I kept this on. On goes the endless battle to end snoring.
Didn't work with galaxy s4 and gear  s2

I like it a lot because it works with my Nexus gear. The only problem I have with it is that it only logs 50 snoring events in one sleep period and then stops logging AND also stops signaling my Gear to vibrate after that...This bug MUST het fixed. Thank you.

content: After help from the devs I got it working with the gear 2 last night.  Unfortunately it just triggers the gears notification and that's not strong enough to interupt me.  But that's not the apps fault.  Would be nice if there was a test button and the app did not have to run in the foreground.  Still the best snore tracker I've tried so far.
